criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria for people living with HIV:

          -  diagnosis of HIv infection for at least 5 years;

          -  use of combined antiretroviral therapy for at least 3 years;

          -  asymptomatic and free from opportunistic diseases at enrollment.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  regular physical exercise;

          -  malnutrition;

          -  presence of coronary artery disease, ischemic diseases, pulmonary disease, diabetes,
             Chagas disease, tuberculosis, heart failure, hypertension;

          -  using pacemakers and/or antidepressant, antiarrhythmic or antihypertensive medication,
             especially beta-blockers.
